description: Deletes network package. A network package is a .zip file in CSAR (Cloud Service Archive) format defines the function packages you want to deploy and the Amazon Web Services infrastructure you want to deploy them on. To delete a network package, the package must be in a disable state. To disable a network package, see UpdateSolNetworkPackage.

parameters.name: nsdInfoId
parameters.description: ID of the network service descriptor in the network package.
